CHANGES0133 — Propagate isClosedProp truncation (Σ → ∃)

Changes since bck0132 (6093 lines → 6143 lines, +50 lines):

The definition of `isClosedProp` in Part01 was changed from a bare `Σ` type
to a propositionally truncated `∃` (= `∥ Σ ∥₁`). This is mathematically
correct: "there merely exists a sequence α such that P ↔ ∀n. α n ≡ false".
All downstream consumers were updated to propagate this change.

Key design: A new postulate `isPropIsClosedPropBare` (Part01) asserts the bare
Σ witness type is a prop. `extractClosedProp` uses `PT.rec` to unwrap the
truncation. This makes the change mechanical: producers wrap in `∣ ∣₁`,
consumers extract with `extractClosedProp {P}`.

Major win: `isPropIsClosedProp` in Part08 was a POSTULATE — now it's PROVEN
as `squash₁` (since `isClosedProp P = ∥ Σ ∥₁` and `∥_∥₁` is always a prop).
This eliminates one postulate.

